</figure>

<p>To start a new task, click the <gui>+</gui> button. The Task Editor window displays. <app>GTG</app> automatically saves the task while you write. When you complete a task, click the <gui>Mark as Done</gui> button in the Task Editor window. The task no longer displays in the <gui>Open</gui> or <gui>Actionable</gui> view modes and is moved to the <gui>Closed</gui> view mode. If the task is no longer relevant, you can dismiss the task. Right-click the task and select <gui>Dismiss</gui> from the task's context menu. This action archives the task.</p> Dismissed tasks are viewable in the <gui>Closed</gui> task view mode.

<p>You can learn more about the features in <app>GTG</app>  by exploring <link xref="index">the main page</link> of this <app>GTG</app> user manual.</p>

